Who Fought? 490 B.C. Persians land 25,000 men north of Athens at Marathon; 
The Persians fought against the Greeks. Persia was ruled by Darius and Xerxes; 
Greeks- Athenians, Spartans, Ionians ... The invasion was a combined land and 
sea invasion. ... After the Athenian defeat many neutral city-states joined Sparta.
